apIpv4Mib.contactinfo: Postal: ArrowPoint Communications Inc. 50 Nagog Park Acton, Massachusetts 01720 Tel: +1 978-206-3000 option 1 E-Mail: support@arrowpoint.com
apIpv4Mib.description: This MIB module describes the ArrowPoint enterprise MIB support for IPv4 Global Information

apIpv4SourceRoute.name: apIpv4SourceRoute
apIpv4SourceRoute.description: If enabled, IP packets with a source route option will be processed. If disabled, they are dropped.

apIpv4RecordRoute.name: apIpv4RecordRoute
apIpv4RecordRoute.description: If enabled, IP packets with a record route option will be processed. If disabled, they are dropped.

apIpv4SubnetBcast.name: apIpv4SubnetBcast
apIpv4SubnetBcast.description: If enabled, IP packets addressed to a broadcast address of a local subnet will be forwarded. If disabled, they are dropped.

apIpv4EcmpMethod.name: apIpv4EcmpMethod
apIpv4EcmpMethod.description: Defines the algorithm to use when multiple equal-cost paths are available to the same destination. 'address' uses the IP addresses to assign a path. 'round' does a simple round-robin.

apIpv4OrphanTimer.name: apIpv4OrphanTimer
apIpv4OrphanTimer.description: The amount of time, in seconds, that a route will be kept after an SCM recovery. Default is 3 minutes.

apIpv4LogRouteChanges.name: apIpv4LogRouteChanges
apIpv4LogRouteChanges.description: If enabled, IP route changes will be displayed in the system log.

apIpv4ReachRoutesMem.name: apIpv4ReachRoutesMem
apIpv4ReachRoutesMem.description: Amount of memory used to maintain reachable routes.

apIpv4TotalRoutes.name: apIpv4TotalRoutes
apIpv4TotalRoutes.description: Current number of routes maintainted, both reachable and unreachable.

apIpv4TotalRoutesMem.name: apIpv4TotalRoutesMem
apIpv4TotalRoutesMem.description: Amount of memory used to maintain all routes.

apIpv4ReachHosts.name: apIpv4ReachHosts
apIpv4ReachHosts.description: Current number of reachable host entries.

apIpv4ReachHostsMem.name: apIpv4ReachHostsMem
apIpv4ReachHostsMem.description: Amount of memory used to maintain reachable host entries.

apIpv4TotalHosts.name: apIpv4TotalHosts
apIpv4TotalHosts.description: Current number of host entries maintainted, both reachable and unreachable.

apIpv4TotalHostsMem.name: apIpv4TotalHostsMem
apIpv4TotalHostsMem.description: Amount of memory used to maintain all host entries.

apIpv4PoolMem.name: apIpv4PoolMem
apIpv4PoolMem.description: Amount of memory held in IP routing table pool.

apIpv4B2BRedundancy.name: apIpv4B2BRedundancy
apIpv4B2BRedundancy.description: Indicates whether box-to-box redundancy is configured on this box.

apIpv4Opportunistic.name: apIpv4Opportunistic
apIpv4Opportunistic.description: Indicates the operating mode for layer-3 opportunistic forwarding. In 'local' mode (the default), packets whose IP address equals a resolved node attached to a local subnet will be forwarded to that node regardless of the destination MAC address of the packet. In 'all' mode, packets whose IP address matches any reachable IP routing entry will be forwarded according to the routing entry regardless of the destination MAC address of the packet. In 'disable' mode, only packets whose destination MAC address equal this node's MAC address will be forwarded using an IP route entry.

apIpv4RedundancyIf.name: apIpv4RedundancyIf
apIpv4RedundancyIf.description: The IP address of the redundant link

apIpv4RedundancyMaster.name: apIpv4RedundancyMaster
apIpv4RedundancyMaster.description: The IP address of the redundant Master

apIpv4RedundancyMasterMode.name: apIpv4RedundancyMasterMode
apIpv4RedundancyMasterMode.description: Indicates whether box-to-box redundancy is configured to always be the master.

apIpv4EcmpSticky.name: apIpv4EcmpSticky
apIpv4EcmpSticky.description: This object specifies whether when making an ECMP decision on the return port, should the ingress port be the preferred path.

apIpv4ImplicitService.name: apIpv4ImplicitService
apIpv4ImplicitService.description: This object specifies whether when configuring a static route, if an implicit service should be started for the next hop address.

apIpv4RedundancyLinkFailTable.name: apIpv4RedundancyLinkFailTable
apIpv4RedundancyLinkFailTable.description: The IP redundancy Interface failure monitor table.

apIpv4RedundancyLinkFailEntry.name: apIpv4RedundancyLinkFailEntry
apIpv4RedundancyLinkFailEntry.description: An entry in the IP redundancy Interface failure monitor table.

apIpv4RedundancyLinkFailIfIndex.name: apIpv4RedundancyLinkFailIfIndex
apIpv4RedundancyLinkFailIfIndex.description: Interface Index used to uniquely identify ethernet interface

apIpv4RedundancyLinkStatus.name: apIpv4RedundancyLinkStatus
apIpv4RedundancyLinkStatus.description: Monitor this interface for physical link failure if true

apIpv4VrrpVRID.name: apIpv4VrrpVRID
apIpv4VrrpVRID.description: This object tells virtual router ID in vrrp protocol.

apIpv4VrrpPriority.name: apIpv4VrrpPriority
apIpv4VrrpPriority.description: This object tells virtual router priority in vrrp.

apIpv4numUplinkServices.name: apIpv4numUplinkServices
apIpv4numUplinkServices.description: This object tells number of uplink services enabled.

apIpv4numViableUplinks.name: apIpv4numViableUplinks
apIpv4numViableUplinks.description: This object tells number of uplink services alive.

apIpv4numPhylinkMarked.name: apIpv4numPhylinkMarked
apIpv4numPhylinkMarked.description: This object tells number of redundant-physical links monitored.

apIpv4toMasterStateCnt.name: apIpv4toMasterStateCnt
apIpv4toMasterStateCnt.description: This object tells number of times the box become master.

apIpv4toBackupStateCnt.name: apIpv4toBackupStateCnt
apIpv4toBackupStateCnt.description: This object tells number of times the box become backup.

apIpv4RedundancyTrap.description: This trap is generated when the state of Redundancy changes.
